description:
What does it really take to retire in your 30s? Business Insider spoke with six everyday Americans who left traditional careers behind to chase freedom, travel, and family time. They share the sacrifices they made and the financial strategies they used to build million-dollar portfolios and achieve early retirement.

00:00 - Intro
00:47 - Financial Struggles and Early Career

09:22 - Lessons, Regrets, and Advice for People Who Want to Retire in Their 30s
10:53 - Advice for Couples
11:52 - Lessons From a Millennial Who Returned to Work After Retiring
13:39 - The Future
15:37 - Credits
